name: Paul Cohen
text: Love this place. Everytime we visit Boston we stop and get a Lobster Roll here. I know there may be many others in New England, but this chain store constantly had good fresh lobster rolls. We tried their Thanksgiving sandwich too. Also very good. Friendly service.

name: Bonnie Miller
text: This was the first time I've been to a D'Angelo's and thought, "Hey, this is actually pretty good." Prior to this, I couldn't think of a single item on the menu I even liked. But we stopped at the rest stop for a quick bite, and I ordered …More

name: Carl P.
text:
I kindly requested NO mushrooms! I have a severe allergy to mushrooms! Sure enough I got mushrooms on my sandwich.
Not good.   They can run into problems for doing such things.

name: Darryl Curtis
text: The Steak Bomb, was okay. It was more of a dud than a bomb. It took a long time to get, but the place is "wait for it" understaffed, busy and has sporadic spurts of customers.

name: Brett Suriner
text: Haven't gotten a slice of Papa Gino's in a long time so I had a combo 2. Best pizza I've eaten at a Papa Gino's in a decade. The fountain drinks had half out of order, so I grabbed a Pepsi. Worst fountain drink I've had in ages. Get a bottle of something, avoid the fountain drinks.

text: Typical quick stop sandwich place. Good food.
